snippet.textDisplay:
Killer: The Troll
Lore: 1200’s Germany, crusader comes back from the East, tormented & scarred from what he had seen... and done. Murdering anyone who drew near to where he had retreated to, he was eventually captured by the local lord, who stripped him of his armor, and treated him as a beast, covering him in chains & forcing him to fight others for his amusement. Stuck in the dark for days, weeks, even months at a time sometimes, held down by heavy metal chains, he grew attached to the darkness, hearing it whisper to him, and he listened, believing it to be the voice of God, telling him what to do redeem himself. Clawing at his chains until his fingers bled raw, he screamed, until he could scream no more. One night, with clouds covering a moonless sky, a shrill screech was heard, coming from the noble’s room. When the servants entered, all that was found was a massive puddle of blood, one hand, and broken chains.

Appearance: Heavily muscled, absolute unit of a man, body wrapped in chains & tattered chainmail. Face/Head is scarred, eyes sunken deeply in, but not gone. Long matted hair winds down his back from his head (dreadlocks). Teeth appear jagged in mouth, and nose is bent. Right arm is insanely YUGE, while left has everything gone halfway down from the elbow, blood still leaking from it. Tattered rags cover his legs, along with more chains.

Power: A deep connection to the entity, quite literally connects him to the darkness in every map. He is able to summon a spectral chain, which when charged appears on his stump-arm and makes a rattling noise, alerting nearby survivors. After a 2 second windup, he throws chain towards a survivor, which if landed will drag survivors towards killer until a skill check is passed. Survivors can be pulled over pallets & windows (think literally dragged over). Flashlight can cancel, but is very hard to make. Killer can move at 90% speed while survivor is on chain, but is unable to reel them in while moving. Survivors are reduced a health state every ten seconds they are dragged. Normal M1 is a morning star/mace. (Think Crusader)
